  "prompt": "I'm going through a midlife crisis at 18. What should I do?",
  "response": "It\u2019s not uncommon to feel a sense of confusion, uncertainty, or even crisis at 18, even though the term \"midlife crisis\" typically applies to older adults. This period of your life is a major transitional phase, where you\u2019re figuring out your identity, future, and place in the world. Here are some steps to help you navigate this challenging time:\n\n### 1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings**\n   - It\u2019s okay to feel lost or overwhelmed. Recognizing and validating your emotions is the first step toward addressing them.\n   - Journaling or talking to someone you trust can help you process what you\u2019re experiencing.\n\n### 2. **Explore Your Identity and Values**\n   - Take time to reflect on what truly matters to you. What are your passions, interests, and values?\n   - Experiment with different hobbies, activities, or career paths to discover what excites you.\n\n### 3. **Set Small, Achievable Goals**\n   - Break down larger aspirations into smaller, manageable steps. This can help you feel more in control and accomplished.\n   - Celebrate the progress you make, no matter how small.\n\n### 4. **Seek Support**\n   - Talk to friends, family, or a mentor about how you\u2019re feeling. Sometimes, an outside perspective can provide clarity.\n   - If your feelings are overwhelming, consider speaking with a therapist or counselor who can help you work through them.\n\n### 5. **Embrace the Process of Self-Discovery**\n   - It\u2019s okay not to have everything figured out at 18. Life is a journey, and it\u2019s normal to make mistakes and change directions along the way.\n   - Focus on learning about yourself and growing, rather than comparing your path to others\u2019.\n\n### 6. **Take Care of Your Physical and Mental Health**\n   - Prioritize sleep, exercise, and a healthy diet to support your overall well-being.\n   - Practice mindfulness, meditation, or relaxation techniques to manage stress and anxiety.\n\n### 7. **Challenge Unrealistic Expectations**\n   - Society often puts pressure on young people to have their lives together by a certain age, but this is unrealistic.\n   - Remind yourself that it\u2019s okay to take your time and explore different paths.\n\n### 8. **Focus on the Present Moment**\n   - Instead of worrying about the future or dwelling on the past, try to live in the present. Mindfulness practices can help with this.\n   - Appreciate the small joys and experiences in your daily life.\n\n### 9. **Be Open to Change**\n   - Your goals, interests, and priorities may evolve over time, and that\u2019s perfectly normal. Embrace change as part of your growth.\n\n### 10. **Remember You\u2019re Not Alone**\n   - Many people experience similar feelings at your age, even if they don\u2019t talk about it openly. You\u2019re not the only one going through this.\n\nThis is a time of exploration and growth, and it\u2019s okay to feel uncertain. Be patient with yourself, and know that it\u2019s all part of the journey toward building a fulfilling life.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
